snippet.textDisplay: I've watched DissociaDID several times and I am so grateful for that collective resource because they are a wealth of knowledge, as well as the others Anthony found. The other collectives/systems seemed absolutely amazing and I loved hearing their feedback/story. I unfortunately have an ungrad psychology professor who very poorly explained DID in a mannerism similar to the "I have a different personality at work then I do at home" comment and sitting in that class during that lecture really irked me. Not to mention my own experience with other severe mental disorders (ex: Schizophrenia, etc.) and having that same professor explain them in a same poor way. And honestly I hate movies and material that don't do their full research before production (ex: Split, Psycho, Schizo, etc.) and/or use DID or other complex issues (ex: trans identity/politics, childhood trauma, drug abuse/addiction, etc.) for horror shock (ex: Silence of the Lambs, The Shining etc.). Now I love horror, but using mental disorders and/or conditions of the mind that specifically have individuals more likely statistically to be abused/killed versus being the abuser/killer plot focus in material is kinda disgusting. And not to say I ban horror, but I'm saying media today should be more aware of their content.

@23:11. She's so adorable and endearing and I love how understanding, paitent and accepting he was/is of everyone, but espcially her and that she was safe. He even was willing to do anything needed like cutting Segments from this meeting with her, or entirely; Anything she and they all needed.
I know It's vulernable and brave as hell that this was kept. And I have to say...Thank you all. Her message is so important and please know I am sending love, because she was so brave and so comforting. I'm glad he gave her a hug because I was straight up crying..
Both for what they've been through (Not that I know everything of course), and for that message. Thank you to Kyle and Nin for theirs too and the other Systems who responded to this question, as well as this Video as a whole..
But the answers to that question really hit me hard...Damn it I wish I could talk to these beautiful people in person. They are helping more than they even know.
Love to them all. To Anthony as well, for such an amazing Interview and being the kind hearted person that he is as well.

I apologize this isn't a really short comment like many in this day and age prefer... But hopefully it conveys how this Interview has made me feel.
Any passionate comment from me is always going to be way longer than most these days prefer shrugs
